# Force LF line endings for shell scripts so they execute correctly under
# WSL/Linux even on Windows checkouts. Without this, git's autocrlf=true
# (default on Windows) silently converts to CRLF on checkout and bash chokes
# on the trailing `\r` after every line — broke peter-channel/launch.sh on
# 2026-05-21 (commit 7d055e0).
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
launch.sh text eol=lf
